item.title: Kauai Makerspace
item.dc:creator: russell.vea
item.content:encoded:
Our goal at the Kauai Makerspace is to create a community powered workspace that fosters creative technological exploration, education, and invention.
With a facility of conducive of productivity and education, we can encourage and support the sharing of knowledge within our community by making advanced tools and equipment accessible to all.

iLab is a collaborative open space at the heart of Manoa campus that students from schools such as engineering, business, architecture, CTAHR, natural science, theatre and others can all take advantage of. Equipped with 3D printers and 3D scanners, iLAB offers an interactive environment where you can express, present, and collaborate on your ideas and inventions.
